FOUR men were today due in court after drugs worth £286,000 were seized following early morning raids in Glasgow. Drugs worth £300,000 seized in Glasgow raids FOUR men were today due in court after drugs worth £286,000 were seized following early morning raids in Glasgow.Police searched units at Glenwood industrial estate, Castlemilk, and three homes in Dougrie Place, Cressland Drive and Drakemire Avenue at 8am yesterday.They said a quantity of suspected cocaine, ecstasy and heroin had been recovered.Two men aged 20 and two aged 25 and 53 have been arrested.A report is due to go to the Procurator Fiscal. 